    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generally refers to the style and culture of the Chiadma ethnic group in Morocco, who dwell mainly on the Atlantic coast between Safi and Essaouira. Specifically, may refer to a style of pile rug by the Chiadma tribal weavers noted for a unique mixture of medallions, borders, and motifs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
